Basically agree with you, however reputations are far less than people think.<br>
Anyone that is a greedy SoB only has to post up an apology later in that toons life and they will be given another shot. Reps have little consequence until players are much higher level and still display those traits.<br>
Look at any high level guild, they have atleast 2-3 people that were known as &quot;loot-whores&quot; during lower levels. NBG is still crock as far as I am concerned, it only works with people you know are honorable.<br>
Take your example:<br>
Once the Enchanter says, &quot;No, we random.&quot; The other party members should roll, if they win they give the item to the bard. Now the bard has a 5 in 6 chance of getting it.<br>
Any looting system is exploitable, but NBG, caters to those who would exploit their group for profit.<br>
