<br>
On established servers, people doing the Frenzy that are not melee are there for it's trade value, or more than likely to twink.<br>
<br>
On KB there's not a real huge trade market at the moment, as people are either busy leveling or just camping the stuff that they want.<br>
<br>
In this situation I'd say NBG has to have it, if I camp the frenzy and a FBSS drops, as a Shammy I'd have no use for it, if the group did a full random sure I'd roll on it, and if I win I'd give it to the warrior in the group probably, or Monk, or whoever I thought deserved it most.<br>
<br>
My point is, on KB, the only reasons I'd be at the Frenzy as a Shammy would be xp or to help a guildy get their sash.  If I want to camp for loot, I'll camp for something I can use straight away and not have to muck about trading for.<br>
<br>
For all you other support chars out there that say 'I'm a chanter/cleric, they NEED me to do Frenzy so I should get to roll'  Just remember that next time you're camping for a chanter/cleric drop and the tank uses the same excuse.<br>
<br>
NBG should stick imho, I will never roll on NBG unless I will truly use the item on the char I am playing at that time.<br>
